    "attributes": {
        "action": "Appoint an independent panel to conduct a Public Inquiry into the DVSA",
        "additional_details": "This should investigate concerns of the misuse of powers and the improper obstruction of complaints resulting in staff complained about not being held accountable for gross injustice & labelling.\r\n\r\nThe scope should include but not limited to historic unresolved complaints:\r\n \r\nHow many Drivers/Driving Instructors have lost their job\r\nWhether drivers have been wrongly removed from the DVSA register\r\nAny impact caused e.g. hardship, pain, stress & anxiety\r\n \r\nThe public require an honest complaint system.\r\n \r\nwww.ombudsman.org.uk/about-us/how-our-casework-makes-difference/case-summaries/641\r\nwww.theguardian.com/uk-news/2018/dec/03/black-women-far-less-likely-than-white-men-to-pass-driving-tests",
        "background": "We call on the Government to appoint an independent panel to carry out a full public inquiry into the Driver & Vehicle Standards Agency. ",
